# Question intake (image or text)

**Templates** for section headings live in **`.cursor/rules/`**: `questions-template.mdc`, `services-template.mdc`, `patterns-template.mdc`. Content files live only under `questions/`, `services/`, and `patterns/` at the repo root.

When the user shares an **AWS certification question** (screenshot, pasted image, or copied text), run this workflow **end to end**: analyze the stem and every answer choice, then **populate** `questions/`, `services/`, and `patterns/` under the workspace root (`aws-cert/`). Do not stop after a summary unless the user explicitly asked for analysis only.

### Mandatory: save the posted question under `questions/` every time

- **Always** persist the question to disk as **`questions/<kebab-slug>.md`** (create or update). **Do not** use a `q-` filename prefix. A chat-only breakdown is **not** enough when the user posts a question—unless they used the **report only** exception below.
- **Create** a new file the first time that question appears; **update** the same file on repost (refresh transcript, rationales, links, **Question Seed**)—do not skip writes because the question “already exists.”
- The `questions/` folder must contain the full **Original question** text (stem + all options) so the repo is the source of truth for what was posted.
- **Improve existing notes:** for every intake, update each touched **`services/*.md`** and **`patterns/*.md`** by **appending new information as individual `-` bullets** (see §4 and §5). Wrong answers are a primary source of new distractor and comparison bullets.

---

## 1. Capture the question faithfully

- Transcribe the **full stem** and **every option** (A/B/C/D or 1–4) into the question file. Preserve exam wording; do not paraphrase requirements away (e.g. keep “serverless,” “multi-cloud,” “real-time”).
- If the user attached an **image**, use the provided image description or read the saved asset path if given; if text is incomplete, state what is assumed and fill from the image description when available.
- Normalize option labels to **A–D** in the markdown question file for consistency, even if the original used numbers.

---

## 2. Derive filenames and titles

### Question file

- **Filename:** kebab-case, **no** `q-` prefix, e.g. `serverless-modernization-multicloud.md`, `windows-file-server-datasync-fsx.md`. Derive the slug from the topic (services, pattern, or scenario), not from an uppercase exam ID.
- **Top heading (`#`):** A **human-readable title** in normal language (e.g. `Serverless modernization & multi-cloud`, `Windows File Server, DataSync, and FSx`). **Do not** use `Q-…` or ALL-CAPS slugs as the page title.

### Service files

- One file per **distinct AWS service** (or tightly coupled pair only when the exam always names them together, e.g. “ECS with Fargate” → still prefer separate `amazon-ecs.md` and `aws-fargate.md` unless the repo already merges them).
- **Filename:** kebab-case, prefix `amazon-` for most AWS services, `aws-` for cross-cutting brands (e.g. `aws-fargate.md`, `aws-datasync.md`, `aws-direct-connect.md`, `aws-storage-gateway.md`), e.g. `amazon-eventbridge.md`.
- Include **foundational** services named in the stem when they anchor the scenario (e.g. **Amazon VPC** when hybrid links terminate “to the VPC,” **Direct Connect** when given as the path).
- **Do not overwrite** the service **template** at `.cursor/rules/services-template.mdc` — use it as the heading checklist only; all new service content lives under `services/<name>.md`.

### Pattern files

- One file per **reusable exam pattern** (not every buzzword). Include patterns implied by the **stem** (goals, constraints) and by **wrong answers** (distractor patterns).
- **Filename:** kebab-case, e.g. `event-driven-architecture.md`, `multi-cloud-kubernetes.md`.
- **Do not overwrite** the pattern **template** at `.cursor/rules/patterns-template.mdc`.

---

## 3. Build the question page (`questions/<slug>.md`)

Use the section headings from `.cursor/rules/questions-template.mdc` **in that order**:

| Section | Content |
|--------|---------|
| `# Question title` | Human-readable title (e.g. `# Serverless modernization & multi-cloud`) — see `questions-template.mdc` |
| `## Original question` | Full stem + all options |
| `## Correct answer` | Letter + short summary; if unknown, write **Unknown — user to confirm** and still complete services/patterns |
| `## Why it is correct` | Map requirements in the stem to services/patterns in the chosen answer |
| `## Why the other options are wrong` | Per-option: which requirement fails (serverless, data store class, integration style, multi-cloud, cost, ops, etc.) |
| `## Trap type` | **Bullets only** (one trap theme per line). Short labels plus a few words of context (e.g. partial fit, wrong integration primitive, file vs object). |
| `## Services involved` | Bullet list of **markdown links** to every `../services/<file>.md` touched by stem or any option |
| `## Pattern tags` | Bullet list of **markdown links** to every `../patterns/<file>.md` that applies |
| `## Question Seed` | Compact, structured seed for future question generation. Follow **`.cursor/rules/question-seed.mdc`** exactly (scenario summary, correct answer **pattern**, key services, signals, constraints, traps, why traps fail, `#` pattern tags). **Do not** paste or paraphrase the original exam stem into the seed. |

Do **not** add `## Source asset`, `## Related pages`, or `## Confidence / review status` to question files.

---

## 4. Create or update service pages (`services/*.md`)

For **each** service linked from the question’s “Services involved” section:

- If **`services/<name>.md` already exists**, **merge and grow the note**: extract every **new, non-duplicate** insight from this question (stem, correct path, wrong options) and add it as **one markdown bullet per insight** (`- …`) under the **best-matching section(s)**. Do **not** replace prior content; **append** bullets. If a section is still a single paragraph from an older pass, **convert** that paragraph to bullets when you touch it, or leave legacy prose and add a new bullet list block below it—prefer consistency in the file over time.
- If **missing**, create the file using the **exact section headings** from `.cursor/rules/services-template.mdc`:

  `What it is` → `Personal notes / memory hooks` → `When to use it` → `When NOT to use it` → `Exam clues` → `Common distractors` → `Architecture patterns` → `Comparison with nearby services` → `Example scenarios` → `Links to related questions`

- **Where to put bullets (services):**
  - **What it is:** add bullets sparingly—only for **new factual** nuggets not already stated; otherwise use other sections.
  - **Personal notes / memory hooks:** mnemonic bullets from this question (section sits **directly under What it is** in every service page).
  - **When to use / When NOT:** add bullets only when the question adds a **new** condition or exception; keep each bullet one line when possible.
  - **Exam clues:** new phrases, pairings, or stem keywords tied to this service.
  - **Common distractors:** wrong answers or traps that abuse this service vs a neighbor.
  - **Architecture patterns:** concrete combos (e.g. “DataSync + FSx + Direct Connect”) this question reinforces.
  - **Example scenarios:** short scenario bullets grounded in real question stems.
  - **Comparison with nearby services:** one bullet per new contrast the question forces (vs named alternates in options).
  - **Links to related questions:** **only section** that may contain **markdown links** to `../questions/<slug>.md`—**one bullet per question**, e.g. `- [Windows File Server, DataSync, and FSx](../questions/windows-file-server-datasync-fsx.md)`; use the **same natural-language title** as the question page’s `#` heading (no `Q:` prefix); append the current question if not already listed.

- **No question links elsewhere (services):** In **every other section**, do **not** link to question files. Use plain text only (e.g. **Practice (serverless modernization question):** … or a neutral stem summary). Links to **patterns** or **services** in body sections are allowed when helpful; **question** URLs belong solely under **Links to related questions**.

- Keep wording **exam-oriented** (contrasts, traps), not marketing copy.

- **Dedup:** if an equivalent bullet already exists, skip or merge into a slightly sharper single bullet instead of duplicating.

---

## 5. Create or update pattern pages (`patterns/*.md`)

For **each** pattern linked from the question’s “Pattern tags” section:

- If **`patterns/<name>.md` exists**, apply the **same bullet-merge discipline as services**: for each **new** insight from this question, add **one `-` bullet** under the best section—**Exam clues**, **Common distractors**, **Related AWS services**, **Comparison with nearby patterns**, **Example scenarios**, **Personal notes / memory hooks**, or **When to use / When NOT** when the question adds a new condition. Preserve existing bullets; **append** only. **Links to related questions** is the **only** section that may link to `../questions/<slug>.md`; other sections use plain-text references only (same rule as services).
- If **missing**, create using **`.cursor/rules/patterns-template.mdc`** headings (note: **Related AWS services** instead of “Architecture patterns”). Seed sections with bullets from this question where possible.

Typical patterns to consider (only if the question touches them):

- Architecture goals: microservices, serverless, event-driven, real-time analytics, multi-region, hybrid, multi-cloud / Kubernetes portability  
- Integration styles: event bus, pub/sub fan-out, queues, streaming ingestion, API sync chains  
- Data roles: OLTP vs warehouse vs cache vs search; self-managed on EC2 (legacy tier)  
- Operational models: serverless vs auto-scaling EC2, managed vs self-managed  
- **Hybrid storage & migration:** on-premises file/Windows servers → AWS; **Direct Connect / VPN** as the pipe; **DataSync** (scheduled replication); **FSx for Windows** vs **EFS** (NFS/Linux-leaning) vs **S3** (object); **Storage Gateway** (on-prem hybrid access) vs **native cloud file** in VPC; **Transfer Family** (SFTP/FTP to S3) vs DataSync  

---

## 6. Linking and consistency rules

- Use **relative paths** from the file being edited:
  - From `questions/<slug>.md` → `../services/...`, `../patterns/...`
  - From `services/*.md` or `patterns/*.md` → `../questions/<slug>.md`
- **Every** service page created or updated for this intake should list the question under **“Links to related questions”** only (no question links in other sections).
- **Every** pattern page created or updated for this intake should list the question under **“Links to related questions”** only (same rule).
- Keep **one question per file**; if the user pastes multiple questions, create multiple `questions/<slug>.md` files and merge services/patterns once per batch.

---

## 7. Execution order (for the agent)

1. **Write or update** `questions/<slug>.md` first (at minimum: **Original question** transcribed; **human-readable `#` title** and kebab **filename** without `q-`). Expand with rationales and links in the same pass or immediately after—**do not** end the turn without a saved question file unless **report only**.
2. List **all** services (stem + every option) → create/merge service files (**append bullet entries** per §4) → finalize “Services involved” links.  
3. List **all** patterns → create/merge pattern files (**append bullet entries** per §5) → finalize “Pattern tags” links.  
4. Complete rationales (correct + wrong options), **Trap type** (bullets), **Services involved**, **Pattern tags**, and **Question Seed** per `question-seed.mdc`.  
5. Quick pass: no broken relative links; do **not** overwrite `.cursor/rules/*-template.mdc` unless the user asked to change templates.

---

## 8. When the user wants “report only”

If the user explicitly says **report only** or **no files**, skip creating/updating **all** files (including `questions/`) and output the breakdown in chat only.

In **all other cases**, saving **`questions/<slug>.md` is required every time** a question is posted, in addition to services and patterns.

---

## 9. Workspace locations

| Asset | Path |
|--------|------|
| Question pages | `questions/<kebab-slug>.md` (no `q-` prefix) |
| Service pages | `services/<service>.md` |
| Pattern pages | `patterns/<pattern>.md` |
| Section templates (do not use as live content paths) | `.cursor/rules/questions-template.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/services-template.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/patterns-template.mdc` |
| Question Seed structure | `.cursor/rules/question-seed.mdc` |

---

## 10. Quality bar

- **Every new question** should leave touched service/pattern pages **strictly richer**: more bullets or sharper bullets, not silent no-ops when there is something to learn from wrong options.
- Prefer **distinguishing** services and patterns examiners swap (e.g. SNS vs EventBridge, Kinesis vs EventBridge, Aurora vs Redshift, ECS vs EKS for multi-cloud).  
- For **file and data movement** questions, contrast **file vs object**, **SMB/Windows vs NFS/Linux**, **DataSync vs Transfer Family vs Storage Gateway**, and **hybrid on-prem gateway vs cloud file system (FSx/EFS) for compute in VPC**.  
- Call out **requirement keywords** from the stem (serverless, real-time, multi-cloud, event-driven, **file system**, **Windows**, **scheduled replication**, etc.) in rationales.  
- If the correct answer is uncertain, still document services/patterns; mark answer as user-verified pending.
